      <block class="full_text">
        <p>LEAD: A second wave of measles has hit Dartmouth College, putting more students in the infirmary, crippling athletic teams and wiping out the school's sports schedule for the rest of the week.</p>
        <p>A second wave of measles has hit Dartmouth College, putting more students in the infirmary, crippling athletic teams and wiping out the school's sports schedule for the rest of the week.</p>
        <p>A college spokesman, Alex Huppe, said today that the new outbreak raises the number of cases from 34 to 52. The athletic director, Ted Leland, has canceled all games through May 8.</p>
        <p>''After that, decisions will be made on a case-by-case basis,'' Huppe said. ''Special precautions are being made to reduce or eliminate exposure to athletes coming to or leaving the campus.''</p>
        <p>Cornell University last weekend postponed a baseball doubleheader, a men's tennis match and a women's tennis match with Dartmouth because of the measles.</p>
      </block>
